FT  26 JAN 93 / Newcastle phone sales base planned
MATRIXX Marketing, a wholly owned subsidiary of Cincinnati Bell, the
American telecommunications company, is to set up its UK telephone sales
base at Newcastle Business Park, Tyne and Wear. It is expected to create up
to 100 jobs during the next three years.
The Department of Trade and Industry is providing Pounds 95,000 regional
selective assistance towards the Pounds 900,000 start-up costs of the
operation, which is Matrixx's second outside the US. The Tyne and Wear
Development Corporation is contributing Pounds 80,000 towards rental costs.
